Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_left_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_left_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_left.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_left-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_right_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_right_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_right.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_right-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_top_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_top_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_top.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_top-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Manganaro: [Σ?]ιμ̣ύλου\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>Manganaro: [Κ]αλλιπίδα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>(tomb) of Simylos son of Kallipidas\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The name Simylos is attested at Tauromenion and Akrai in the Hellenistic period, making it the most likely restoration of the name in line 1 (although one might note that both Κωμύλος (Catania) and Μύλος (Monte Saraceno) are also attested on the island). The piece appears to be part of an epitymbion funerary monument, of a type common in Hellenistic Sicily, including along the north coast of the island (e.g. at Cefalu).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 49.1272 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1999 42 no.22 fig.97 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001813\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001813\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Plain square letters of regular size without serifs. Mu has vertical first and last, midstrokes descending almost to the line; Alpha appears to have straight bar. Pi has equal length hastae, with overlapping top bar.\u003C/p> Line 1-2  50  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[217,220,223,226,229,232,235,238],{"id":218,"html":219},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag, April 2006\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σιμύλου\n                    Καλλιππίδα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σιμύλου\">[Σι?]μύλου̣\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Καλλιππίδα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Καλλιππίδα\">[Κ]α̣λλι̣ππίδα̣\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag, April 2006\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σιμύλου\n                    Καλλιππίδα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σιμύλου\">[..]ΜΥΛΟ.\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Καλλιππίδα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Καλλιππίδα\">[.].ΛΛ.ΠΠΙΔ.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":221,"html":222},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_left_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_left_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_left.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_left-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_right_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_right_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_right.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_right-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_top_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_top_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003473_top.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-05\" src=\"ISic003473_top-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":224,"html":225},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Manganaro: [Σ?]ιμ̣ύλου\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>Manganaro: [Κ]αλλιπίδα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":227,"html":228},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>(tomb) of Simylos son of Kallipidas\u003C/p>  ",{"id":230,"html":231},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The name Simylos is attested at Tauromenion and Akrai in the Hellenistic period, making it the most likely restoration of the name in line 1 (although one might note that both Κωμύλος (Catania) and Μύλος (Monte Saraceno) are also attested on the island). The piece appears to be part of an epitymbion funerary monument, of a type common in Hellenistic Sicily, including along the north coast of the island (e.g. at Cefalu).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":233,"html":234},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 49.1272 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1999 42 no.22 fig.97 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001813\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001813\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":236,"html":237},"handnote","\u003Cp>Plain square letters of regular size without serifs. Mu has vertical first and last, midstrokes descending almost to the line; Alpha appears to have straight bar. Pi has equal length hastae, with overlapping top bar.\u003C/p> Line 1-2  50  Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":239,"html":240},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[242,244,247,248],{"html":243},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag, April 2006",{"id":245,"lang":142,"html":246},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σιμύλου\n                    Καλλιππίδα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σιμύλου\">[Σι?]μύλου̣\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Καλλιππίδα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Καλλιππίδα\">[Κ]α̣λλι̣ππίδα̣\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":243},{"id":249,"lang":142,"html":250},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σιμύλου\n                    Καλλιππίδα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σιμύλου\">[..]ΜΥΛΟ.\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Καλλιππίδα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Καλλιππίδα\">[.].ΛΛ.ΠΠΙΔ.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[252,254,257,259,262,264,267,269,272,274],{"image":104,"thumb":253,"title":107},"ISic003473_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":255,"thumb":256,"title":107},"ISic003473.jpg","ISic003473-thumb.jpg",{"image":110,"thumb":258,"title":107},"ISic003473_left_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":260,"thumb":261,"title":107},"ISic003473_left.jpg","ISic003473_left-thumb.jpg",{"image":113,"thumb":263,"title":107},"ISic003473_rear_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":265,"thumb":266,"title":107},"ISic003473_rear.jpg","ISic003473_rear-thumb.jpg",{"image":116,"thumb":268,"title":107},"ISic003473_right_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":270,"thumb":271,"title":107},"ISic003473_right.jpg","ISic003473_right-thumb.jpg",{"image":119,"thumb":273,"title":107},"ISic003473_top_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":275,"thumb":276,"title":107},"ISic003473_top.jpg","ISic003473_top-thumb.jpg",[278],{"html":57},"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Funerary monument of (?)Simylos\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>original data collection and editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JCu\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728\">James Cummings\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>conversion to EpiDoc\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n\t    \u003CrespStmt>\n     \t       \u003Cname xml:id=\"SS\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569\">Simona Stoyanova\u003C/name>\n     \t       \u003Cresp>standardisation of template and tidying up encoding\u003C/resp>\n \t   \u003C/respStmt>\n            \u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic003473\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\">644942\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\">70900809\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\">336066\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003473\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"DOI\" when=\"2020-12-23\">10.5281/zenodo.4388634\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>S. Marco d'Alunzio\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"museum\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/054\">Museo della cultura e\n                            delle Arti Figurative Bizantine e Normanne\u003C/repository>\n                       \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">2\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>A quadrangular base, with a moulding around the lower edge, and the socket for a cylindrical column in the upper surface. The block is damaged on all sides, but parts of each face are preserved, showing that the moulding ran round all four sides, and only the front face was engraved. The block is most likely not a column capital, as suggested by Manganaro, but the base of an epitymbia style funerary monument. The inscribed face is preserved to a maximum width of 47cm. Dimensons recorded include the moulding, which projects c.5cm on each face. The stone appears to be the local breccia.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/2.html\">stone\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.funerary_monument\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/230.html\">funerary monument\u003C/objectType>                                    \u003Cdimensions>\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">25\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">70\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">68\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.damaged\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Two lines of large Greek letters across the face above the moulding, of which the beginnings and ends are lost.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.incomplete\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Plain square letters of regular size without serifs. Mu has vertical first and last, midstrokes descending almost to the line; Alpha appears to have straight bar. Pi has equal length hastae, with overlapping top bar.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Line 1-2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"50\" atMost=\"50\">50\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462228\">Haluntium\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2523425\">San Marco d'Alunzio\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>38.07261, 14.70093\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"-0200\" notAfter-custom=\"-0001\" evidence=\"lettering\">later hellenistic\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\">Record as a casual find on via Colombo, which traverses the upper part of the hill on which the modern town stands, not far below the summit.\u003Cgeo>38.0728781,14.6995279\u003C/geo>. Now on display in the town museum.\u003C/provenance>\u003C!-- representative point on via Colombo -->\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\" xml:id=\"autopsy\">Prag, April 2006\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003C